Enum Card

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Card>
      card.core.Card
All Implemented Interfaces:

public enum Card
extends java.lang.Enum<Card>
implements java.util.Comparator<Card>

Card is an enum with 52 values. Typical value SIX_HEART which is, of course, is the six of hearts. There are no jokers -- just the 13 cards of each suit (clubs, hearts, diamonds, spades).

compare

public int compare(Card c1,
                   Card c2)
Since Card class implements Comparator a 'compare' method must be provided. Compare two card values by comparing their numerical values. At present suit is not considered. Since suit is an enum its values are comparable too. Note that many card games do not order the suits but it may be convenient to do so in order to break ties. When this is done no two cards are "equal".

Specified by:
compare in interface java.util.Comparator<Card>
Parameters:
c2 - - Card to compare "this" to.
Returns:
int value as prescribed by Comparable.
